Tidy a svy_vglm model

Source: R/custom_tidiers.R
tidy_svy_vglm.Rd

A tidier for models generated with svyVGAM::svy_vglm(). Term names will be updated to be consistent with generic models. The original term names are preserved in an "original_term" column. Depending on the model, additional column "group", "component" and/or "y.level" may be added to the results.

Usage

tidy_svy_vglm(x, conf.int = TRUE, conf.level = 0.95, ...)

Arguments

x

(svy_vglm)
A svyVGAM::svy_vglm() model.

conf.int

(logical)
Whether or not to include a confidence interval in the tidied output.

conf.level

(numeric)
The confidence level to use for the confidence interval (between 0 ans 1).

...

Additional parameters passed to parameters::model_parameters().

See also

Other custom_tidiers: tidy_broom(), tidy_multgee(), tidy_parameters(), tidy_vgam(), tidy_with_broom_or_parameters(), tidy_zeroinfl()
